# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: MagePath12
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "The next day came quick."
    new "The next day came quick."

    old "Sarah sneaked out of the bed, leaving Samayra to sleep, as she went to the study."
    new "Sarah sneaked out of the bed, leaving Samayra to sleep, as she went to the study."

    old "Sarah got out of bed and went to the study."
    new "Sarah got out of bed and went to the study."

    old "Arriving in the study, she found Xan already awake, waiting by the window, looking out at the city."
    new "Arriving in the study, she found Xan already awake, waiting by the window, looking out at the city."

    old "You'd never know it by these people that a great civilization ended yesterday."
    new "You'd never know it by these people that a great civilization ended yesterday."

    old "You didn't seem to care much either when we were there."
    new "You didn't seem to care much either when we were there."

    old "Xan kept staring out the window."
    new "Xan kept staring out the window."

    old "Maybe. But then again, I've seen what it once was. What was left of it when we got there was just a shadow."
    new "Maybe. But then again, I've seen what it once was. What was left of it when we got there was just a shadow."

    old "What a beautiful city. But all things fade I suppose."
    new "What a beautiful city. But all things fade I suppose."

    old "So now we're back."
    new "So now we're back."

    old "Countless dead, a city in ruins, and what did it all get us?"
    new "Countless dead, a city in ruins, and what did it all get us?"

    old "Xan turned around."
    new "Xan turned around."

    old "Everything we came for, really. So on that front we can't be too upset."
    new "Everything we came for, really. So on that front we can't be too upset."

    old "Xan waved his hands towards the table."
    new "Xan waved his hands towards the table."

    old "Resting atop it was the fate stone, still glimmering with that mysteries crimson light."
    new "Resting atop it was the fate stone, still glimmering with that mysteries crimson light."

    old "Sarah remembered discovering it. All the things the spirit spoke of came back to her. How much of it was true..."
    new "Sarah remembered discovering it. All the things the spirit spoke of came back to her. How much of it was true..."

    old "Of course, you bringing along your girlfriend was not part of the plan."
    new "Of course, you bringing along your girlfriend was not part of the plan."

    old "Sarah ignored his barb."
    new "Sarah ignored his barb."

    old "It's a stone. A shiny one, but that hardly seems worth having gone through all that."
    new "It's a stone. A shiny one, but that hardly seems worth having gone through all that."

    old "Ooh, it's quite a bit more than just a shiny stone."
    new "Ooh, it's quite a bit more than just a shiny stone."

    old "But don't trouble yourself over it."
    new "But don't trouble yourself over it."

    old "You always tell me this."
    new "You always tell me this."

    old "Xan looked up in surprise."
    new "Xan looked up in surprise."

    old "You always say, don't question, don't ask. You never tell me much of anything."
    new "You always say, don't question, don't ask. You never tell me much of anything."

    old "I barely have any idea what we're doing half the time, and you just keep asking me to trust you. What if I don't?"
    new "I barely have any idea what we're doing half the time, and you just keep asking me to trust you. What if I don't?"

    old "You don't trust me?"
    new "You don't trust me?"

    old "I don't know anymore."
    new "I don't know anymore."

    old "Yes, you're probably right. I've been thinking about this for a while now."
    new "Yes, you're probably right. I've been thinking about this for a while now."

    old "Thinking about what?"
    new "Thinking about what?"

    old "You've been my apprentice for a few years now. I've taught you plenty, but lately I've been starting to think that my mentorship is holding you back."
    new "You've been my apprentice for a few years now. I've taught you plenty, but lately I've been starting to think that my mentorship is holding you back."

    old "Sarah stared at Xan as he spoke the words."
    new "Sarah stared at Xan as he spoke the words."

    old "I've been thinking that it might be best for me to send you to the citadel."
    new "I've been thinking that it might be best for me to send you to the citadel."

    old "The...the citadel?"
    new "The...the citadel?"

    old "Sarah had heard of the place many times before, but had never been there before."
    new "Sarah had heard of the place many times before, but had never been there before."

    old "The home of the order of mages. The place that existed somewhere outside of this world altogether. An endless library."
    new "The home of the order of mages. The place that existed somewhere outside of this world altogether. An endless library."

    old "This was the home of the council that governed the order, and who handed down their decrees and instructions."
    new "This was the home of the council that governed the order, and who handed down their decrees and instructions."

    old "I think it will be good for you."
    new "I think it will be good for you."

    old "Just for a few years. You can study, be removed from this world. You can learn to let go, not be so attached."
    new "Just for a few years. You can study, be removed from this world. You can learn to let go, not be so attached."

    old "It sounded like a nightmare to Sarah."
    new "It sounded like a nightmare to Sarah."

    old "I have no place there. I belong in this world, not some dusty library surrounded by old men who study books for centuries on end."
    new "I have no place there. I belong in this world, not some dusty library surrounded by old men who study books for centuries on end."

    old "Sarah, I keep telling you this but you're not listening."
    new "Sarah, I keep telling you this but you're not listening."

    old "You're too attached, too much in-this-world. Your stay in the citadel will help you."
    new "You're too attached, too much in-this-world. Your stay in the citadel will help you."

    old "Sarah decided to push back."
    new "Sarah decided to push back."

    old "And if I don't want to?"
    new "And if I don't want to?"

    old "Well, I wasn't asking for your opinion, it's already been decided. You're going."
    new "Well, I wasn't asking for your opinion, it's already been decided. You're going."

    old "For all her training and her power. It didn't amount to anything. She was still a plaything in someone else's design."
    new "For all her training and her power. It didn't amount to anything. She was still a plaything in someone else's design."

    old "The last of the preparations are being made, but in a few days, I will take you to the citadel. Trust me, it will all be for the best."
    new "The last of the preparations are being made, but in a few days, I will take you to the citadel. Trust me, it will all be for the best."

    old "Sarah didn't bother to listen to him defend himself. She stormed out."
    new "Sarah didn't bother to listen to him defend himself. She stormed out."

    old "Betray Xan"
    new "Betray Xan"

    old "She knew Xan would never change his mind. Nor could she fight him."
    new "She knew Xan would never change his mind. Nor could she fight him."

    old "Not alone, at least."
    new "Not alone, at least."

    old "A thought emerged, and Sarah took off towards the room at the end of the hall. The room that housed Razaphel."
    new "A thought emerged, and Sarah took off towards the room at the end of the hall. The room that housed Razaphel."

    old "Sarah called out, she had no temper to wait."
    new "Sarah called out, she had no temper to wait."

    old "The spirit emerged from it's flask, much more swiftly than usual."
    new "The spirit emerged from it's flask, much more swiftly than usual."

    old "Aah, my new friend..."
    new "Aah, my new friend..."

    old "Sarah stepped forward, towards the spirit."
    new "Sarah stepped forward, towards the spirit."

    old "No, I don't have any time for you and your words today."
    new "No, I don't have any time for you and your words today."

    old "You seem upset."
    new "You seem upset."

    old "Xan just told me he was going to take me to the citadel..."
    new "Xan just told me he was going to take me to the citadel..."

    old "You would be wise not to go. Whatever he told you, it was most certainly a lie. The citadel is a bleak place."
    new "You would be wise not to go. Whatever he told you, it was most certainly a lie. The citadel is a bleak place."

    old "But I don't have a choice!"
    new "But I don't have a choice!"

    old "He is more powerful than me, he can force me if I try to resist."
    new "He is more powerful than me, he can force me if I try to resist."

    old "The spirit's body swirled through the air."
    new "The spirit's body swirled through the air."

    old "He can, and he will."
    new "He can, and he will."

    old "Back in Bagrad...we spoke..."
    new "Back in Bagrad...we spoke..."

    old "You said...that I could not trust him...and the gods...you told me so much..."
    new "You said...that I could not trust him...and the gods...you told me so much..."

    old "The spirit never spoke, it's ethereal body only softly twitching."
    new "The spirit never spoke, it's ethereal body only softly twitching."

    old "What if I choose to believe you?"
    new "What if I choose to believe you?"

    old "I mean...if I decided to believe you...would you help me?"
    new "I mean...if I decided to believe you...would you help me?"

    old "A hiss emerged from the creature."
    new "A hiss emerged from the creature."

    old "Yes. Help me keep my freedom. Keep me from being send to the citadel."
    new "Yes. Help me keep my freedom. Keep me from being send to the citadel."

    old "The mage does not listen to my words, I doubt I could convince him where you could not."
    new "The mage does not listen to my words, I doubt I could convince him where you could not."

    old "Sarah knew that the spirit understood her, but he compelled her to speak plainly."
    new "Sarah knew that the spirit understood her, but he compelled her to speak plainly."

    old "Her freedom would depend on it, and for that, she would dare to speak."
    new "Her freedom would depend on it, and for that, she would dare to speak."

    old "I'm not talking about convincing him with words..."
    new "I'm not talking about convincing him with words..."

    old "Aah, so you do not seek me for my wisdom, but for my strength..."
    new "Aah, so you do not seek me for my wisdom, but for my strength..."

    old "Yes. Help me subdue Xan. Together we might be strong enough."
    new "Yes. Help me subdue Xan. Together we might be strong enough."

    old "Together...perhaps."
    new "Together...perhaps."

    old "But you would have me risk a great deal. The mage can throw me back into the void with ease, should we fail."
    new "But you would have me risk a great deal. The mage can throw me back into the void with ease, should we fail."

    old "But we won't fail!"
    new "But we won't fail!"

    old "Sarah pleaded with the spirit, she knew he was her only hope."
    new "Sarah pleaded with the spirit, she knew he was her only hope."

    old "And what do you offer me for my assistance?"
    new "And what do you offer me for my assistance?"

    old "She was desperate."
    new "She was desperate."

    old "I will help you get your freedom, if that is what you want. I'll offer you up my body every night. Tell me, and it will be yours."
    new "I will help you get your freedom, if that is what you want. I'll offer you up my body every night. Tell me, and it will be yours."

    old "Another hiss."
    new "Another hiss."

    old "Very well, let us strike this pact."
    new "Very well, let us strike this pact."

    old "What...what do you want in return?"
    new "What...what do you want in return?"

    old "I will ask you in time, and when I ask, you vow to submit. That promise will be enough for me."
    new "I will ask you in time, and when I ask, you vow to submit. That promise will be enough for me."

    old "Sarah doubted, but she knew she would give everything for her freedom, and only she spirit could give it to her now."
    new "Sarah doubted, but she knew she would give everything for her freedom, and only she spirit could give it to her now."

    old "Fine, I agree to the terms."
    new "Fine, I agree to the terms."

    old "What do we do?"
    new "What do we do?"

    old "Submit and go to the citadel"
    new "Submit and go to the citadel"

    old "Sarah was angry, but she also knew she had no option to fight Xan."
    new "Sarah was angry, but she also knew she had no option to fight Xan."

    old "He was too powerful, and if he wanted to force her there, he would and could."
    new "He was too powerful, and if he wanted to force her there, he would and could."

    old "Sarah returned to her room and fell down against the wall, softly crying."
    new "Sarah returned to her room and fell down against the wall, softly crying."

